---------------------------------------

(1) Squeegee for applying the decal

How to apply*
-------------------
1) Apply decal to a clean smooth wall and gently scrape with a plastic card. This will help the vinyl adhere to the wall.
2) Peel back a small corner of the transfer tape.
3) Pinch the small corner of transfer tape and slowly peel the tape from the vinyl. When peeling back, do not pull the transfer tape away from the wall. Instead, peel the tape by folding it over itself.

You can hang it up in your bathroom for decorative purposes or use to wipe your hands on it. The embroidery graphic sewn on the towel has a tear away stabilizer that it is sewn over. I can get out most of the stabilizer when I use my scissors sometimes I cannot get it all and do not want to force it off and ruin the towel. It does come off as you wash the towel and you can use your fingers to pick it off.
